--[[ Dialogue ]]
mayo_lng_dlg_hello										= "Well if you want fish Mayo doesn't have one but you can\nuse her services as many times as you like. Sigh... the\nOPS department are not paying her enough for this..."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat1										= "Hello to you <#player>. This is Mayo from the OPS Department.\nThe services she offer doesn't require any entitlements so\nfeel free to use them."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat2										= "Mayo only ask for a piece of <#color_blue>"..mayo_config( 1 ).."<#color_def>.\nYou can get the item in the Cell Garden or the lower\nlevels of the Citizen Promenade."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat3										= "Mayo's services is a serious violation of the People's\nCharter obviously."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat4										= "So remember this..."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat5										= "If you report Mayo to the OPS Department, she will bring\ndown her Dioneaea Alpha to one of your missions and\nwill rip out your Will'O Alternator from your corpse."
mayo_lng_dlg_chat6										= "Mayo would love that to happen."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip1									= "There are so many secrets buried within this <#pt>\nPanopticon you know. Just the other day Mayo managed\nto extract a Will'O Alternator intact!"
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip2									= "Intact as in no scratches and no dents at all."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip3									= "But it was a pain dragging that thing around without\nalerting the <#pt> Panopticon you know."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip4									= "Sign..."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip5									= "Ssshh you shaz. Shut up! There are eyes and ears\neverywhere."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip6									= "You almost tripped the Will'O sensors you shaz."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip7									= "As Mayo is saying, of course she sold it and now she has\nso many entitlement points that she have no idea what to\ndo with it."
mayo_lng_dlg_gossip8									= "Mayo can only laugh at its previous owner whoever that\nwas. Good riddance she says."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol11								= "<#color_blue>"..mayo_lng_btn_resource_shungite.."<#color_def> is a highly concentrated Will'O resource\nmainly used as a tool for modifying weapons. Useless\nwhen the weapon being modified is already at level 8."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol12								= "To use, select the weapon you want to increase the rarity\nlevel then select a second weapon to be used as a fodder.\nChoose <#color_blue>"..mayo_lng_btn_resource_shungite.."<#color_def> as the material."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol13								= "When done right the weapon's rarity level is increase.\nRepeat the process until you reach level 8."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol14								= "The benefit of raising a weapon's rarity level is the number\nof modules you can install to it. A rarity 8 weapon can hold\n12 modules."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol21								= "Here is a list of resources used in facilities for reducing\na weapon's base elements."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol22								= mayo_icons( 41 )..mayo_icons( 19 ).." <#color_blue>Will'O Engine: All-Purpose Mk 4<#color_def>\t\t\t\t\t"..mayo_icons( 41 )..mayo_icons( 20 ).." <#color_blue>Will'O Engine: Carrier Mk 4<#color_def>\n"..mayo_icons( 41 )..mayo_icons( 21 ).." <#color_blue>Will'O Engine: Artillery Mk 4<#color_def>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t"..mayo_icons( 41 )..mayo_icons( 22 ).." <#color_blue>Will'O Engine: Red Rage Mk 2<#color_def>"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol23								= "Please note that advanced weapon's base element can't\nbe lowered below the default 30."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol24								= "As an example, an advanced Peltatum will always have a\npermanent base element of 30 "..mayo_icons( 22 ).."."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol31								= "This technique applies to any facilities."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol32								= "The steps are as follows."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol33								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Step #1:<#color_def> Manufacture any Weapons, Augmentations,\n\tCombat Items or Medical Supplies. Wait until the facility\n\tis done manufacturing."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol34								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Step #2:<#color_def> Once done, open the facility and accept the\n\tfinished product by pressing "..mayo_icons( 46 ).."."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol35								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Step #3:<#color_def> When the word <#color_blue>Saving...<#color_def> appears quickly\n\tpress the <#color_blue>Home Button<#color_def> and quit the game."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol36								= "When done right, relaunch the game and you'll have\nextra copy on your inventory and the original copy\nwaiting at the facility."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol37								= "You can do this as many times as you want."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol38								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Author:<#color_def> <#color_blue>Rotten Cheese<#color_def>\n"..mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Youtube Channel:<#color_def> <#color_blue>goo.gl/ciGorn<#color_def>\n"..mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Contributor:<#color_def> <#color_blue>daromu@baidu<#color_def>"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol39								= "For more details visit Rotten Cheese's Utopedia videos.\nHere is the link."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol41								= "NPC weapons are unique and have different loadout method\nunlike your standard weapons."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol42								= "To equip NPC weapons you must first upgrade or modify it.\nWhen asked if you want to equip it simply choose <#color_blue>Equip<#color_def>."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol43								= "Make sure to save the <#color_blue>Loadout<#color_def> to avoid repeating the\nprocess again and messing with the modules."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol51								= "<#color_blue>How the Upgrade Made it Easier to Access Retributions?<#color_def>\nUpgrading the Kulkarni Field to version 1.22 enabled the\nOPS Department to push Retributions to all Sinner cells."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol52								= "The missions are unlimited. A Sinner can finish one mission\nand request the same mission over and over again."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol53								= "All a Sinner have to do is connect to the New York\nPanopticon's server."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol54								= "For the Greater Good!"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol61								= "There are two methods. You can either complete a certain\noperation or attempt to trade with an OPS agent."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol62								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Method #1:<#color_def> Complete the Solo-Operation <#color_blue>CT806\n\tAll-Purpose Biped Mk 4<#color_def>. The main strategy is to “sever\n\tas many parts as possible” in the “shortest time possible.”"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol63								= "It is important to acquire at least one <#color_blue>Rarity 8<#color_def> resource.\nKeep all the resources and you will be given a penalty."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol64								= "This method is only possible if you haven't claimed the\n<#color_blue>Right to Retain Items of Rarity Level 2-8<#color_def> entitlements."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol65								= mayo_icons( 41 ).."<#color_orange>Method #2:<#color_def> All you have to do is to look for an OPS\n\tAgent and attempt to trade items. Get as many penalty\n\tas possible."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol66								= "You can find them on the lower levels of the Citizen\nPromenade."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol67								= "Remember Sinner. Never Contribute."
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol68								= "??/??/102014 PE\n\nTiger “Dog” Garheim"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol69								= "And what is the point of reclaiming sentence you ask?\nNothing. But isn't it cool?"
mayo_lng_dlg_weeklyvol610								= "While most Sinners focus on reducing their sentence you on\nthe other hand defy how this world works. You're a rebel,\nyou're unique, one of the few who stands at the top."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m1										= "Mayo have been asked about this so many times now."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m2										= "She can't blame them though. Few <#player>s have achieved\nthe ultimate sin."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m3										= "For <#player>s to reclaim sentence simply approach an OPS\nAgent and propose a trade. Not Mayo of course but you'll\nfind them slithering about at the Citizen Promenade."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m4										= "What a shaz. Of course Mayo have her own “unique”\nways."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m5										= "Not to mention, OPS Agents either works with Natalia,\nthe elite Blank or the Social Harmony Enforcement\nSquad."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m6										= "OPS Agents can bend rules so to speak. Just try\ndisagreeing with one and you'll see."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m7										= "For more details visit Mayo's Utopedia blog. Here is the\nlink."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m8										= "Just a warning. Reclaiming sentence takes time and it\nmay not worth it for some <#player>s."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m9										= "Also, having a 9 Million sentence on one's head doesn't\ndo anything. It will not make you a better <#player>."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m10										= "Though Mayo admit, it kinda looks cool."
mayo_lng_dlg_9m11										= "For more details, refer to the <#color_blue>Percy Propa Weekly<#color_def> entry."
